locale	: Display language variables 	| 	-a displays all
less	: Per page view
ls 	: list content			|	-l = long  
find	: search for files 		| 	count of files changed last day :
						 find -ctime -1 | wc -l
df [directory] -h: disk space usage (h= human-readable)
rm -i	: remove interactively
rm -rf	: recursively delete filetree (:-[
mkdir/rmdir:	
testdisk: testing physical disk (explore more!)
scalpel	: retrieving deleted files
shred	: =rm but complete with overwrite
trash	: =rm but to trashcan (recovery possible)
cat /proc/sys/kernel/random/entropy_avail : shows entropy of system
gpg	: -c = create | -d =decrypt | no option but filename= extract original file
top	: monitor all processes, update every 2 sec, press f for changing view, press 1 for all processors
vmstat -a 2 100: show memory usage, every 2 secs, a 100 times
pstree	: treeview of all active processes/tasks
ps	: list active processes
at + 1 minutes, hours, days	:schedule a task, enter command, end with CTRL+D  [DOESNT WORK !!!]
echo -e "/007"	: BEEP  [DOESNT WORK !!!]
echo -e \a	: BEEP [DOESNT WORK !!!]
lsmod	: list all modules loaded by kernel
uname -sr	: echo current kernel version
mount	: without arguments, show all mounted filesystems (snap dev proc ....)
